title: Russian submarine commander shot dead on morning run after 'appearing on Ukrainian blacklist'
description: A Russian military official who commanded a submarine in the Black Sea and appeared on a Ukrainian blacklist of alleged war criminals has been shot dead by an unknown assassin while on his morning run.

title: Zelenskyy criticises 'absurd' lack of timetable for Ukraine to join NATO
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy has criticised the "absurd" absence of a timetable for his country to join NATO as leaders met at a summit in Lithuania.

title: 'All of us were screaming': Irish fighter 'Rambo' describes terrifying Russia tank chase in Ukraine
description: If Ukraine's counter-offensive has moved more slowly than many in the West had hoped, it has also proven more costly in terms of human lives.

title: French police have 'no clue' what has happened to toddler missing since Saturday
description: French police searching for a two-year-old boy who went missing from his grandparents' garden in the French Alps on Saturday have said they still have no clues as to what has happened to him.

title: Heatwave to grip southern Europe until at least end of next week
description: A scorching heatwave gripping southern Europe is expected to tip temperatures well into the 40C range this week and next, as many Britons prepare for their summer holidays abroad.

title: EasyJet summer cancellations - what are your rights if your flight is cancelled?
description: EasyJet has cancelled 1,700 flights during the peak summer holiday season.

title: Six killed after tourist helicopter crashes near Everest
description: Six people have been killed in a helicopter crash near Mount Everest after returning from a sightseeing tour.

title: Olympic champion Caster Semenya wins human rights court appeal over athletics testosterone rules
description: Double Olympic champion Caster Semenya has won a human rights court appeal over the rules governing testosterone in athletics competitions.

title: Twitter wins big name backer against Threads - but it's the Taliban
description: Twitter has won the support of a big name backer against fast-growing rival Threads - but it's the Taliban.

title: Weight-loss and diabetes drugs investigated over reports of suicidal thoughts
description: Two drugs used as diabetes and weight-loss treatments are being investigated after some patients reported having suicidal thoughts.

title: Sir Elton John thanks fans after 'magical' last night on tour
description: Sir Elton John has said he is still "trying to process" his last gig after completed his tour after more than 50 years performing across the world.

title: Alarming rise in 'zombie drug' deaths in America, weeks after first UK fatality
description: New figures show a shocking rise in deaths on US streets linked to a drug which rots the skin of those who use it.

title: Despite major lobbying by Kyiv, speedy accession to NATO is very unlikely
description: A giant poster on the road into the host city of this week's NATO summit in Lithuania reads: "Ukraine deserves NATO membership now".

title: Football fan dies after being hit in neck by bottle of beer outside stadium
description: A woman has died in Brazil - two days after she was hit in the neck by a beer bottle during a brawl at a football stadium.

title: Teenager carves his own name into pillar at 8th-century temple in Japan
description: A Canadian teenager has been questioned in Japan after he carved his name into a wooden pillar at an 8th-century temple.

title: Volcano near Iceland's capital erupts for the second time in a year
description: Iceland's Fagradalsfjall volcano, which is around 20 miles away from capital Reykjavik, has begun erupting.
